OL,3,CMPs told of 'suspicions' of UK-wide
OL,4,Cspying on journalists by police
OL,6,F"The PSNI know what journalists are
OL,7,Fspeaking to what politicians, and we
OL,8,Ffeel that is an attack on democracy.
OL,10,F"This isn't just an issue which
OL,11,Fpertains to the journalistic
OL,12,Fcommunity... whether it is
OL,13,Fpoliticians, lawyers, activists,
OL,14,Fjournalists, we feel it is a much
OL,15,Fbroader societal issue and that is why
OL,16,Fit needs a public inquiry."
OL,18,FMr McCaffrey said: "The police need to
OL,19,Fbe held to account, to follow the
OL,20,Frules. It wasn't us who broke the law.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUxD@[O]zD@TOU
